values:
I'm back in area, so thought I'd start reading this thing again cos many of you don't like managing your social life with facebook and so I'll have to see what's going on by reading it here. *effort*

Anyway, look forward to seeing some of you more than I used to!


x

Have aquired a multitude of cds for DigiWon (as apparently people like to truncate it to). Listening to some Phat tunes right now, can't say what they are cos they are secret weapons, let's just say I have got some white hot tracks to share. Will update Thursday. God it's going to be So Much Fun! It will be a quiet one, but Darren, Ewan anbd I will just play great music and play to our mates while drinking.

Listened to Brighteyes - Lifted Or The Story Is In The Soil. Some top tracks on it. "Just want a lover" and "Don't know when but a day is gonna come"

Never feel like posting when I'm down or busy or happily bouncing, which is most states.

Going to reawaken the music journal though as it only died cos of my nights emergence. I was very busy finding and analysing music to play at my night to actually enjoy music of any kind. But now, I am free of such burdens I can listen for pleasure again. (plEEEEzure)

if you want to be added (if you aren't already on the filter) please say so.

goin to bed now, having made my intentions clear.
can someone tell me how to make a default view? there is too much to go through on my friends page.

Got up early to purchase Arcade Fire tickets online, but failed, so lost sleep for nothing. Total bummer.

Decided to snuggle up with a recently downloaded copy of English Patient, but the quality was awful. Bummer.

Have to phone Neil at lunch to apologise for being crazy person last night. Bum.

Woo! It's my day off. Yay.

Sorry for disappearing for so long, but as some of you know, the lead-up to xmas is really important for retail and I was totally run off my feet and very crazed generally.

I had a lovely 3 days of xmas fun at Chris' parents house. I got an Ixus 60 camera for Christmas and was gifted with a personal DAB randomly ("oh, I have one lying around you can have"). We got a 500gb NAS from his parents. Plus I bought my lovely man a Wii, which he is killing his shoulders and back on as we speak; tip: those things really burn calories!

Plan to start my music journal again in the new year (sorry to those of you who actually read it, and thanks for reading it *blush* ).

I just had a giant glass of orange juice; I feel like I have a giant rotting turkey in my gut - really want to detox and cleanse myself. We went to Sainsbury and I bought so much fruit! If anyone has any miracle digestive treatments, please share.

My arms are massive after having to cart huge boxes around for the last 2 months - not sure how I feel about having giant man-arms, but I plan to get myself some punch-pads so I can hit stuff; sometimes I feel like I need to hit stuff.

I plan to have a Phillip K Dick all-nighter, first it was planned for the dvd release of Scanner Darkly, but that unfortunately coincides with Chris' birthday weekend, so now I'm thinking I'll have it on his death-day which is March 2 - although I'm not so sure it's cool to celebrate his death... probably just have it when I can be arsed.

I had a rock and roll week with much clubbing and drinking. woo!
It is the only way to counter working in retail over christmas.

will rejoin LJ when it's all over.

Just quickly, thanks to everyone who came to my party, you all rock. We missed all of you who couldn't make it: special get well shout out to Darren. Hope everyone had a good time :)


x

Immensely upset by this. Tried to sign a petition against it, but couldn't find one. Does anyone know of one? Can any one else find one? Also, if one does not exist, does anyone want to help me start one? I feel incredibly strongly about this and would appreciate any help and support to fight it.

I'm coming to Popstarz on Friday 15th...

...Anyone wanna keep me company?

*coy look*

Is it wrong to apply for other jobs whilst also going for promotion at one's current employment?

*blush*

In other news Chris has turned into stressy-work-guy, closely resembling the "why didn't I do this work earlier in the year?" guy. Damn those focussed Asperger's types. I'm sure I'll have my man back soon. *sigh*

Woo! I've had an amazingly productive day! I wrote a cv, and applied to 5 jobs online. I also wrote the equivalent of a dj-cv in response to a recent email from a guy who is doing a few events in Oct/Nov...*glee*

I also had a long bath, watched a fave film on couch and baked cookies! I've been the best girlfriend to both my lovely boyfriends today too. :)

Hope everyone is well, sorry I've not been around, but I haven't had a day off work that wasn't taken up doing Important Things in a billion years (trying to get new job and hence have more money and free time).

*swings like a sultan*

my computer was involved in a mission of mercy and so I've been without my own computer for a little while. Then I was in mourning over RKB's death... :(

Feel a bit shy coming back to LJ. *waves from behind keyboard*

It is weird how this is everyones primary information trading area, some of my friends I practically only communicate with on lj. hm.

Perhaps we should all write one letter to one person on our friends list, and no not just your close buddy, perhaps someone you would like to be closer with. Friends are great. Some people aren't as lucky as you to have them.
I saw these and had to buy them! Aren't they grotesquely beautiful?! (by the way, I passed my degree)

Wow. I just emailed a guy who runs a club about djing.

We'd spoken about it and he said to email him, so I have. eeeeek!

I would like to say a big thanks to all those who have helped me through this year; there have been many levels of help, some through being there, some through advise, some through simply not abandoning me as many others have. This has been a tough year and I am truly glad for every one of my friends I still have.

*huge hugs*

Don't assume I don't mean you, if you are reading this then at least you haven't unfriended me. Thanks.

A bit of an apology to those I've neglected, normal service will be resumed. Thanks for believing in me.
thanks for leaving your gin. I have discovered that I love it. I am ready to join the ranks of old embittered hags out on out the steps crying, save me a seat.

Oh no!

My favourite show just had an outrageously anti-bisexual episode. Woe is me!

>_<

Until now, I have had nothing to report other than exam nerve angst, which I thought I'd spare you. At work I am moving departments to DVD, which will be a lot more fun, less problematic and is more upwardly-mobile. :)

I am on holiday revising for the next two weeks, my exams are on the 18th and 23rd of May.

It seems *someone* started a rumour that Chris and I were going to break up/had broken up.

This is just not true.

Months ago Chris and I had some difficulties when we first moved in, but we resolved said issues. I would thank you to undo this rumour.

Went to The Mighty Boosh stage show last night at Peterborough. It was pretty good, except every time I laughed I coughed, so I coughed through the entire thing. Peterborough's Broadway Theatre was quite nice, I enjoyed it as a smaller venue as even being at the back isn't that far away. The show had all five cast members, Vince Noir, Howard Moon, Bollo, Nabu and Bob Fossil, and brought out all the favourite characters, Old Gregg, The Cockney Hitcher, The Psychedelic Monk to name a few. They were really good on stage, the scene changes, the use of props - or lack of (they mimed lots), the sound cues were great, there was lots of song and dance - fair amount of interaction with audience, and (my favourite) they broke character a few times also. At one point I found myself detached and able to see that we were at a pantomime for adults - this was about the time the rabbit chased Vince around the theatre and then raped him. Thoroughly enjoyable.
Does a girl really need an excuse to go out and purchase chocolate? "we seem to be running low on milk"

Having good holiday so far, went shopping yesterday and bought not a great deal, but planned outfit for Sunday. Did buy hairdye, a new belt AND an obscenely short skirt. :) Was thinking I'd wear the new skirt to Popstarz Friday, if it is not required for Sunday... much planning required.

Was rudely awakened by Postman, ran downstairs to get my parcel only to find it was just something for next door. :( AND the Postman didn't smile.

Didn't go to gig last night as Chris was feeling stressed out and didn't fancy it  :( this means I missed new material from the band for which I am a groupie. Waaaaaah!

Going to London today for Camden and TCR graphic novel needs. Weeeeeeeeeeee!

Just a quick check: anyone want to be added to Music Journal filter?

Had a lovely weekend! I was not at work so i spent most of Saturday cooking and cleaning with gusto, later entertained guests with wine and indian meal. Party spilled over into Sunday where we spent day watching dvds - I'd recommend United States of Leland, for fans of films such as Donnie Darko and American Beauty. Made spaghetti with meatballs for Neil and Chris, drank wine and went to bed after much spodding. I'd give this weekend a 7/10. Thankyou to all who popped round.

On Parker's Piece...


...And out my window
We got snow! Will post pics soon... [EDIT] Parker's Piece in the snow 2005
Hope everyone has a lovely time over the holidays with friends and family and enjoys the exchange of love and gifts.

Went to Soul Tree on Wednesday. New World Record were a bit crap, the lead man couldn't sing - even in a soulful-i-can't-sing way. Anyway, I had gone to see The Resistance, who were Really Good - again. I have plans to go up to The Cavern in Liverpool in May when they play there - like a proper groupie. :) Their music makes me feel so euphoric, the gorgeous static, such full, warm sounds... Technically, the headliners were Stellastarr; they were well produced, but boring soulless indie rock. Today my recommend would be Jesus & The Mary Chain - Psychocandy, or Suicide - Suicide. Going to download Silver Apples and Can today as Amazon said I would like them.

I get to see my Dad today! :)

*jumps, runs and yelps around like excited puppy*

In LOve

Wow, you two, are in love....Nothing can ever
separate you two... good luck later.

How in love are you with somone?

I'm well and bouncy! Wooooo!

*sings We Are Scientists loudly*

Thanks for all your support over the last few days.

(don't forget to add/remove yourself from my music diary)
Now stilton icecream is just plain wrong. Going to give breakfast a chance. Toast and herbal tea.

Felt fine in afternooon, once empty, so went to xmas dinner at Christ's College. 'twas really nice, good food, good company. Played Cranium in MCR - and won - of course. Chris and I are a lethal combination in board games. Felt a bit dodgy after dinner, but went to bed fine. Woke up late and am still ill. At least it means that any food I ate last night I didn't absorb! Pork fat? nope. Raspberry sorbet? nope. Carbs/fat from au gratin potatoes? nuhuh. This illness is doing my body wonders, in a twisted sort of way. Boss was cunt on phone about me being still ill, but then he said he was only saying what he was required to tell me from staff handbook, so I guess it wasn't his fault. Going to try and not eat anything today (problem is my body wants me to eat - i am really hungry). Neil was sacked yesterday by his best friend. He and his mate run a night at a club, where Neil DJ's (Soul Tree). *pauses to go to loo for 25th time today* His "friend" said he has got some one else to DJ from now on, so tonight will be his last night there. Neil took it well considering. As far as i know, he didn't cut himself. However, he didn't cry or get angry like I would have - i think he silently blames himself and thinks he is crap now - which he isn't. Either way, it means I have to go out tonight - and it WILL be awkward and I will have to be ultra-supportive. It is not going to be a good night. Going to watch more dvds today. Perhaps Summer of Love which got me for my birthday. :) Hope everyone is having great days
This is a test to see who can see my public entries: I have been having problems with my lj recently. if you could reply I will know...

Sorry I have been short with people this week; I have had a bit of a bad week at work. I now have a billion managers pulling me in different directions. yay! I am also going to be 24 on Sunday which has led me to the inevitable analysis of ones achievements and goals in life. Also, being a paranoic I assume everyone will stand me up and show their non-comradeship for me on my birthday. Problem is most people I have invited have confirmed off lj, so making the gathering appear miniscule on my journal. Plus, my darling sexy sister is coming on this excursion; So all my friends get to meet her finally! woo! I really needed hugs so much this week, I've been feeling shit. I will need them all the more in the coming week. Still thinking about my life and so forth and feeling crap about it. Hope everyone had lovely weekends

*meep*

no one is going to come clubbing with me because I am evil and no one cares.

:(

In other news i saw Harry Potter and it was amazing.

I went to Kambar on Friday. This was the first time I had been clubbing alone. Once there i saw people who I knew and got to know better, I even made new friends. yay! I was surprised how well it turned out. Spoke to my sister on the way to club. She is at the point where she is thinking about having children. Strangely, I feel ok about it, proud even. If I can't have children, she should. I mean, it does emphasise my own failure, but if it means she succeeds then it is ok. I feel so stupid having let class and pride get in the way of my dreams. Had a really bad day Saturday as I was tired and kept saying stupid things that offended people; ended up crying in the toilets. I was so angry at myself for having no filter between my thoughts and my mouth. grrrr. Sunday was excellent! my friend came round and picked up my broken drum for re-skinning. It was good to see him, he is having a good and busy time. Then a work friend came round for HDD swapping fun. we got pizza and watched a couple of dvd's. One of which was Closer in which I was scared to find my double in Natalie Portman. Today I am going to tidy up, work on getting my head round Reason s'more and then go into town for lunch. Not sure if I am out tonight or not. Hope everyone has a super day.

Had an interesting night. Gigs were bland and the joint was empty, which led to violent tantrums from the dj; causing a broken toe, a sprained wrist and a mildly annoyed speaker. stayed up Way Too Late, got 3 hrs sleep before work.

Work! Recently at a Work Do I was told I see "short", "terse" and/or "spiky". I can imagine your smug looks right now. Well, I was unaware this was how I was being perceived and took it a little badly. I felt low about it, but in my dynamic way, decided to repair damaged relations and really put lots of effort and attention on my work. I am now having a much better time, really enjoying myself.

Musically, still analysing myself to find my musical core and find myself as a musician; it is a time-consuming, thought intensive process. Might lj some of my thoughts in a filtered thread so you can see my development. Woo!

My birthday is on Sunday 27th Nov, would like to do things with folks on Friday/Saturday - clear your schedules if you love me enough.

x

I recently added a future dated post to my journal which had contact details. Only then, lj said I had to back-date all my entries I made subsequently. So i have been. Only this meant no one could read my entries. I wondered why no one was replying to my life...

anyway, if you could take a moment to read over the last few brief entries that were "missed" due to accounting err0rz, that would meant alot to me as I am PMTing today.
